            </li>
            <li>
                returning less than or equal to zero from the event handler associated with an event action mimics skip action
            </li>
            <li>
                returning the value which is greater than zero from the event hander associated with an event action mimics terminal action. Care should
                be taken that the value returned really represents an existing terminal symbol code. Since scanners are obviously invoked by syntax analyzers,
                although indirectly by the call of lexical analyzers, invalid terminal codes should cause syntax errors.
            </li>
